07/06/2010
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Customs personnel seized 35 million cigarettes Sunday (June 6th) which allegedly were being smuggled from China to EU countries. The shipment was found on a vessel that was being searched in the Black Sea port of Varna. The cigarettes were made to look like a Spanish brand and were packed in 3,500 boxes. Authorities had been investigating and tracking the ship for three weeks. (AFP, 24 Chasa, BNR, Trud - 06/06/10)
